<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4FEF6456" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4E9065E3" blockId="54.[151,980,711,737]" box="[151,980,711,737]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<heading id="56709A5AFFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4E9065E3" bold="true" box="[151,980,711,737]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" reason="1">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4E9065E3" bold="true" box="[151,980,711,737]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4E6065E3" authority="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[151,804,711,737]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FF3CFD6D4F5D65E3" bold="true" box="[151,537,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens</emphasis>
Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC4FFD8FF3CFCB84FEF6456" blockId="54.[151,1436,786,1292]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FF3CFCB84C7A642E" bold="true" box="[151,318,786,812]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Composition.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FE2AFCB84FBA6429" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[385,766,786,811]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE2AFCB84FBA6429" box="[385,766,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is composed of three species: 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FA83FCB84C406451" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FA83FCB84C406451" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FEB8FC904CD16451" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus australis Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[275,405,826,851]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FEB8FC904CD16451" box="[275,405,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FE7DFC904FE06451" box="[470,676,826,851]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="odontoglossum">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE7DFC904FE06451" box="[470,676,826,851]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. odontoglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="459D7EBDFFC4FFD8FF6DFCC84E44620E" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC4FFD8FF6DFCC84CFD636E" blockId="54.[151,1436,786,1292]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FF6DFCC84C02647E" bold="true" box="[198,326,866,892]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FE21FCC84E436479" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[394,775,866,891]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE21FCC84E436479" box="[394,775,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pseudoscopelus astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is diagnosed from its congeners by the unique photophore and dentition patterns: luminescent tissue present as discrete photophores (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FB59FC20485564A1" box="[1266,1297,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">vs.</emphasis>
completely absent in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FEA2FC184C2864C9" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[265,364,946,971]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aphos">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FEA2FC184C2864C9" box="[265,364,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. aphos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and as vestigial white lines in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FD70FC184E7B64C9" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus parini Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[731,831,946,971]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parini">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FD70FC184E7B64C9" box="[731,831,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. parini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FCF1FC184EC064C9" box="[858,900,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">mxf</emphasis>
short, restricted to area below orbit, not connected to 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FEA3FC704C6964F1" box="[264,301,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">apf</emphasis>
posteriorly (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE6FFC704F5264F1" box="[452,534,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">vs. mxf</emphasis>
absent or if present connected to 
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FC34FC704E8064F1" box="[927,964,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">apf</emphasis>
posteriorly); elongate canine teeth present on basihyal and second basibranchial (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FD26FBA84FE96319" box="[653,685,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">vs.</emphasis>
teeth absent on basihyal; small conical teeth present on second basibranchial); palatine teeth 
<typeStatus id="D23C9394FFC4FFD8FE5DFB804F6C6346" box="[502,552,1066,1092]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
4, with considerable ability to bend caudally (
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FBF3FB8049336341" box="[1112,1143,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">vs.</emphasis>
palatine teeth of 
<typeStatus id="D23C9394FFC4FFD8FAE1FB8048386346" box="[1354,1404,1066,1092]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
1, firmly attached to bone).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D382D36FFC4FFD8FF6DFBD04E44620E" blockId="54.[151,1436,786,1292]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FF6DFBD04C8B6396" bold="true" box="[198,463,1146,1172]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Ontogenetic changes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FE7CFBD14FBB6396" authorityName="Prokofiev and Kukuev, 2006 Pseudoscopelus australis Prokofiev and Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[471,767,1147,1172]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE7CFBD14FBB6396" box="[471,767,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Pseudoscopelus australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a negative, statistically significant allometric growth of the pectoral fin (P&lt;0.05, 
<figureCitation id="95BC31B3FFC4FFD8FE74FB084F0763BE" box="[479,579,1186,1212]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1275,1299]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,835,1245]" captionTargetId="figure-350@18.[151,1436,830,1248]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 8. Graphic of the species of Pseudoscopelus which allometric pectoral-fin growth is allometric in relation to the standard length is statistically significant: (A) positive growth (P=0.001) in P. scriptus (blue squares); (B) negative growth (P=0.042) in P. obtusifrons (black triangles); (C) negative growth (P&lt;0.001) in P. australis (red dots)" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8 C</figureCitation>
); because of limited samples available, it could not be determined if this is also true in 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FE94FB614F5063E6" authorityName="Prokofiev &amp; Kukuev" authorityYear="2006" box="[319,532,1227,1252]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="astronesthidens">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FE94FB614F5063E6" box="[319,532,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. astronesthidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA8756B5FFC4FFD8FDE4FB614E5963E6" box="[591,797,1227,1252]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="odontoglossum">
<emphasis id="3FF3F124FFC4FFD8FDE4FB614E5963E6" box="[591,797,1227,1252]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">P. odontoglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="95BC31B3FFC4FFD8FC84FB604ECC63E6" box="[815,904,1226,1252]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="48.[151,255,1427,1451]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,303,1415]" captionTargetId="figure-210@48.[151,1436,303,1415]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 21. Schematic drawing of the photophore pattern in lateral and ventral vies of (A) Pseudoscopelus scutatus, ISH 567b-c/1966, 80.4 mm, paratype; (B) P. bothrorrhinos, SIO 07-6, 39.6 mm, paratype." pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Dentition pattern of specimens was formed in specimens as small as 
<quantity id="CA7F80D3FFC4FFD8FE17FB584F61620E" box="[444,549,1266,1292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.19" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="31.9">31.9 mm</quantity>
(CAS-SU 66492).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
